⚠️ The 2990WX NUMA Problem — This Is Likely Killing Your Speed
The Threadripper 2990WX has a notorious architectural flaw. It has 4 dies, but only 2 of them have memory controllers (dies 0 and 2). The other two are "compute-only dies" (dies 1 and 3) that must route all memory access through the memory dies over Infinity Fabric.
Die 0 [mem ✓] ←→ Die 1 [no mem ✗]  ← memory latency 2–3×
Die 2 [mem ✓] ←→ Die 3 [no mem ✗]  ← memory latency 2–3×
Your 20 actor processes, spawned sequentially, will likely land across all 4 dies. The half running on dies 1 & 3 are operating with severely degraded memory bandwidth — and llvmpipe software rendering is extremely memory-bandwidth bound. This alone can cut your effective actor throughput by 30–50%.

