libGL error: failed to load driver: nouveau
X Error of failed request: GLXBadContext
The environment variables for software rendering (LIBGL_ALWAYS_SOFTWARE=1, GALLIUM_DRIVER=llvmpipe) existed in the host shell but Singularity containers don't inherit host environment variables automatically.
Evidence: cat singularity_run_cpu.sh showed no --env flags being passed to Singularity.
Fix: Patched singularity_run_cpu.sh to explicitly pass env vars into containers:
bashsingularity exec -i -n --network=none -p \
  -B `pwd`:/jackal_ws/src/ros_jackal \
  -B ${buffer_path}:${buffer_path} \
  --env LIBGL_ALWAYS_SOFTWARE=1 \
  --env GALLIUM_DRIVER=llvmpipe \
  --env QT_QPA_PLATFORM=offscreen \
  --env DISPLAY=:99 \
  --env BUFFER_PATH=${buffer_path} \
  ${1} /bin/bash /jackal_ws/src/ros_jackal/entrypoint.sh ${@:2}

Issue 7: Deadlock — Actors and Learner Waiting on Each Other
Problem: Occurred twice. Actors wait for policy_latest.pt before generating transitions. Learner waits for 2,000 transitions before saving policy_latest.pt. Neither moves.
Root cause first time: Learner saved initial policy to /dev/shm/local_buffer/ but actors inside Singularity bind-mount the disk local_buffer/ directory, not /dev/shm.
Fix first time: cp /dev/shm/local_buffer/policy_latest.pt local_buffer/policy_latest.pt
Root cause second time: Same issue recurring after full restart because local_buffer/policy_latest.pt was deleted during cleanup.
